      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALDEBARAN EMJAY (2) started a hot favourite on debut at Geelong last week and looked very good, drawing wider than this and racing parked before cruising home by more than 18m. Should enjoy better favours from this lower draw. That could see her hard to contain again. IM FRANKEE (7) was a beaten favourite when 3m away as runner-up in last week's heat but she had shown ability in winning at Menangle in her only other outing. Draws wide but could be up to overcoming that. BUMPER CROP (6) made it two from two when winning from the ace draw at this circuit and distance last week. Draws wider but came from a similar barrier when she scored on debut at Terang prior so could deliver again. KYVALLEY DIXON (3) is open to improvement after she came from this barrier to place when making her debut last week. Russell Jack's CONNECT THE DOTS (5) finds a tough race for her debut but has trialled well so watch the betting.",
